{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":3317,"text":"Interpreter: Piano, \"p,\"\nis my favorite musical symbol."},{"time":7504,"text":"It means to play softly."},{"time":10007,"text":"If you're playing a musical instrument\nand you notice a \"p\" in the score,"},{"time":14194,"text":"you need to play softer."},{"time":16120,"text":"Two p's -- even softer."},{"time":18804,"text":"Four p's -- extremely soft."},{"time":26353,"text":"This is my drawing of a p-tree,"},{"time":29780,"text":"which demonstrates"},{"time":31114,"text":"no matter how many thousands\nupon thousands of p's there may be,"},{"time":35627,"text":"you'll never reach complete silence."},{"time":38477,"text":"That's my current definition of silence:"},{"time":41279,"text":"a very obscure sound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44976,"text":"I'd like to share a little bit"},{"time":46483,"text":"about the history\nof American Sign Language, ASL,"},{"time":49673,"text":"plus a bit of my own background."},{"time":53851,"text":"French sign language was brought\nto America during the early 1800s,"},{"time":59091,"text":"and as time went by,\nmixed with local signs,"},{"time":63190,"text":"it evolved into the language\nwe know today as ASL."},{"time":67168,"text":"So it has a history of about 200 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71800,"text":"I was born deaf,"},{"time":75244,"text":"and I was taught to believe\nthat sound wasn't a part of my life."},{"time":80662,"text":"And I believed it to be true."},{"time":85318,"text":"Yet, I realize now\nthat that wasn't the case at all."},{"time":89272,"text":"Sound was very much a part of my life,"},{"time":92081,"text":"really, on my mind every day."},{"time":98483,"text":"As a Deaf person living\nin a world of sound,"},{"time":102494,"text":"it's as if I was living\nin a foreign country,"},{"time":105438,"text":"blindly following its rules,\ncustoms, behaviors and norms"},{"time":109704,"text":"without ever questioning them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121460,"text":"So how is it that I understand sound?"},{"time":126282,"text":"Well, I watch how people\nbehave and respond to sound."},{"time":130654,"text":"You people are like my loudspeakers,\nand amplify sound."},{"time":134300,"text":"I learn and mirror that behavior."},{"time":136782,"text":"At the same time,\nI've learned that I create sound,"},{"time":139757,"text":"and I've seen how people respond to me."},{"time":142600,"text":"Thus I've learned, for example ..."},{"time":144480,"text":"\"Don't slam the door!\""},{"time":148350,"text":"\"Don't make too much noise when\nyou're eating from the potato-chip bag!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":151771,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":152795,"text":"\"Don't burp,"},{"time":154087,"text":"and when you're eating,"},{"time":155292,"text":"make sure you don't scrape\nyour utensils on the plate.\""},{"time":158158,"text":"All of these things\nI term \"sound etiquette.\""},{"time":163927,"text":"Maybe I think about sound etiquette"},{"time":166382,"text":"more than the average hearing person does."},{"time":169963,"text":"I'm hyper-vigilant around sound."},{"time":175463,"text":"And I'm always waiting\nin eager nervous anticipation"},{"time":179353,"text":"around sound, about what's to come next."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181459,"text":"Hence, this drawing."},{"time":184280,"text":"TBD, to be decided."},{"time":187724,"text":"TBC, to be continued."},{"time":190819,"text":"TBA, to be announced."},{"time":196793,"text":"And you notice the staff --"},{"time":198683,"text":"there are no notes contained in the lines."},{"time":200898,"text":"That's because the lines\nalready contain sound"},{"time":204570,"text":"through the subtle smudges and smears."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208863,"text":"In Deaf culture,\nmovement is equivalent to sound."},{"time":217617,"text":"This is a sign for \"staff\" in ASL."},{"time":220325,"text":"A typical staff contains five lines."},{"time":223904,"text":"Yet for me, signing it\nwith my thumb sticking up like that"},{"time":226702,"text":"doesn't feel natural."},{"time":228053,"text":"That's why you'll notice in my drawings,\nI stick to four lines on paper."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233199,"text":"In the year 2008, I had the opportunity\nto travel to Berlin, Germany,"},{"time":237212,"text":"for an artist residency there."},{"time":240041,"text":"Prior to this time,\nI had been working as a painter."},{"time":245020,"text":"During this summer, I visited\ndifferent museums and gallery spaces,"},{"time":249099,"text":"and as I went from one place to the next,"},{"time":251105,"text":"I noticed there was no visual art there."},{"time":254618,"text":"At that time, sound was trending,\nand this struck me ..."},{"time":259909,"text":"there was no visual art,"},{"time":261911,"text":"everything was auditory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265482,"text":"Now sound has come into my art territory."},{"time":269168,"text":"Is it going to further\ndistance me from art?"},{"time":273800,"text":"I realized that doesn't\nhave to be the case at all."},{"time":276520,"text":"I actually know sound."},{"time":277695,"text":"I know it so well"},{"time":280361,"text":"that it doesn't have to be something\njust experienced through the ears."},{"time":283723,"text":"It could be felt tactually,"},{"time":286732,"text":"or experienced as a visual,"},{"time":288639,"text":"or even as an idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293048,"text":"So I decided to reclaim ownership of sound"},{"time":296333,"text":"and to put it into my art practice."},{"time":301016,"text":"And everything that I had been\ntaught regarding sound,"},{"time":304619,"text":"I decided to do away with and unlearn."},{"time":309099,"text":"I started creating a new body of work."},{"time":312961,"text":"And when I presented this\nto the art community,"},{"time":315539,"text":"I was blown away with the amount\nof support and attention I received."},{"time":320676,"text":"I realized:"},{"time":323669,"text":"sound is like money,"},{"time":327179,"text":"power, control --"},{"time":330375,"text":"social currency."},{"time":335782,"text":"In the back of my mind, I've always felt\nthat sound was your thing,"},{"time":339670,"text":"a hearing person's thing."},{"time":344014,"text":"And sound is so powerful"},{"time":346513,"text":"that it could either\ndisempower me and my artwork,"},{"time":350293,"text":"or it could empower me."},{"time":353138,"text":"I chose to be empowered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356969,"text":"There's a massive culture\naround spoken language."},{"time":361233,"text":"And just because I don't use\nmy literal voice to communicate,"},{"time":366524,"text":"in society's eyes\nit's as if I don't have a voice at all."},{"time":372945,"text":"So I need to work with individuals\nwho can support me as an equal"},{"time":376887,"text":"and become my voice."},{"time":380523,"text":"And that way, I'm able to maintain\nrelevancy in society today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384789,"text":"So at school, at work and institutions,"},{"time":387235,"text":"I work with many\ndifferent ASL interpreters."},{"time":391254,"text":"And their voice becomes\nmy voice and identity."},{"time":396365,"text":"They help me to be heard."},{"time":402380,"text":"And their voices hold value and currency."},{"time":412178,"text":"Ironically, by borrowing out their voices,"},{"time":414540,"text":"I'm able to maintain\na temporary form of currency,"},{"time":418385,"text":"kind of like taking out a loan\nwith a very high interest rate."},{"time":426052,"text":"If I didn't continue this practice,"},{"time":428173,"text":"I feel that I could just\nfade off into oblivion"},{"time":431030,"text":"and not maintain\nany form of social currency."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437488,"text":"So with sound as my new art medium,"},{"time":440167,"text":"I delved into the world of music."},{"time":443089,"text":"And I was surprised to see\nthe similarities between music and ASL."},{"time":449186,"text":"For example,"},{"time":450727,"text":"a musical note"},{"time":453103,"text":"cannot be fully captured\nand expressed on paper."},{"time":456783,"text":"And the same holds true\nfor a concept in ASL."},{"time":461610,"text":"They're both highly spatial\nand highly inflected --"},{"time":470213,"text":"meaning that subtle changes"},{"time":472394,"text":"can affect the entire meaning"},{"time":474927,"text":"of both signs and sounds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479898,"text":"I'd like to share with you\na piano metaphor,"},{"time":482144,"text":"to have you have a better\nunderstanding of how ASL works."},{"time":485153,"text":"So, envision a piano."},{"time":488299,"text":"ASL is broken down into\nmany different grammatical parameters."},{"time":492771,"text":"If you assign a different parameter\nto each finger as you play the piano --"},{"time":496855,"text":"such as facial expression, body movement,"},{"time":501884,"text":"speed, hand shape and so on,"},{"time":505680,"text":"as you play the piano --"},{"time":507912,"text":"English is a linear language,"},{"time":509773,"text":"as if one key is being pressed at a time."},{"time":512602,"text":"However, ASL is more like a chord --"},{"time":516274,"text":"all 10 fingers need\nto come down simultaneously"},{"time":519682,"text":"to express a clear concept or idea in ASL."},{"time":525548,"text":"If just one of those keys\nwere to change the chord,"},{"time":529598,"text":"it would create a completely\ndifferent meaning."},{"time":532152,"text":"The same applies to music\nin regards to pitch, tone and volume."},{"time":540518,"text":"In ASL, by playing around with these\ndifferent grammatical parameters,"},{"time":544120,"text":"you can express different ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545837,"text":"For example, take the sign TO-LOOK-AT."},{"time":548240,"text":"This is the sign TO-LOOK-AT."},{"time":552699,"text":"I'm looking at you."},{"time":556056,"text":"Staring at you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557380,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":561103,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":563733,"text":"Oh -- busted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566423,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":569608,"text":"Uh-oh."},{"time":573521,"text":"What are you looking at?"},{"time":577410,"text":"Aw, stop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578762,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":580455,"text":"I then started thinking,"},{"time":581663,"text":"\"What if I was to look at ASL\nthrough a musical lens?\""},{"time":585011,"text":"If I was to create a sign\nand repeat it over and over,"},{"time":588242,"text":"it could become\nlike a piece of visual music."},{"time":592016,"text":"For example, this is the sign for \"day,\""},{"time":595676,"text":"as the sun rises and sets."},{"time":599789,"text":"This is \"all day.\""},{"time":604416,"text":"If I was to repeat it and slow it down,"},{"time":607641,"text":"visually it looks like a piece of music."},{"time":612023,"text":"All ... day."},{"time":615186,"text":"I feel the same holds true\nfor \"all night.\""},{"time":621776,"text":"\"All night.\""},{"time":623890,"text":"This is ALL-NIGHT,\nrepresented in this drawing."},{"time":630501,"text":"And this led me to thinking\nabout three different kinds of nights:"},{"time":637827,"text":"\"last night,\""},{"time":640747,"text":"\"overnight,\""},{"time":645549,"text":"(Sings) \"all night long.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":648327,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":655861,"text":"I feel like the third one has\na lot more musicality than the other two."}]},{"cues":[{"time":659230,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":661413,"text":"This represents how time\nis expressed in ASL"},{"time":664472,"text":"and how the distance from your body\ncan express the changes in time."},{"time":668955,"text":"For example,"},{"time":670618,"text":"1H is one hand, 2H is two hand,"},{"time":673781,"text":"present tense happens closest\nand in front of the body,"},{"time":677035,"text":"future is in front of the body\nand the past is to your back."},{"time":684209,"text":"So, the first example\nis \"a long time ago.\""},{"time":688209,"text":"Then \"past,\""},{"time":692538,"text":"\"used to\""},{"time":694255,"text":"and the last one, which is my favorite,"},{"time":696314,"text":"with the very romantic\nand dramatic notion to it,"},{"time":698964,"text":"\"once upon a time.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":700577,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":705962,"text":"\"Common time\""},{"time":708703,"text":"is a musical term"},{"time":710495,"text":"with a specific time signature\nof four beats per measure."},{"time":715614,"text":"Yet when I see the word \"common time,\""},{"time":717450,"text":"what automatically comes to mind for me\nis \"at the same time.\""},{"time":721645,"text":"So notice RH: right hand, LH: left hand."},{"time":725578,"text":"We have the staff\nacross the head and the chest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728221,"text":"[Head: RH, Flash claw]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":729427,"text":"[Common time]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":730701,"text":"[Chest: LH, Flash claw]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":733712,"text":"I'm now going to demonstrate\na hand shape called the \"flash claw.\""},{"time":738722,"text":"Can you please follow along with me?"},{"time":741723,"text":"Everybody, hands up."},{"time":746776,"text":"Now we're going to do it\nin both the head and the chest,"},{"time":749498,"text":"kind of like \"common time\"\nor at the same time."},{"time":755595,"text":"Yes, got it."},{"time":757329,"text":"That means \"to fall in love\"\nin International [Sign]."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760168,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":762069,"text":"International [Sign], as a note,"},{"time":763996,"text":"is a visual tool to help communicate"},{"time":766765,"text":"across cultures and sign languages\naround the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769997,"text":"The second one I'd like\nto demonstrate is this --"},{"time":772307,"text":"please follow along with me again."},{"time":778891,"text":"And now this."},{"time":785358,"text":"This is \"colonization\" in ASL."}]},{"cues":[{"time":788082,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":791407,"text":"Now the third --"},{"time":792702,"text":"please follow along again."},{"time":799072,"text":"And again."},{"time":804970,"text":"This is \"enlightenment\" in ASL."},{"time":807502,"text":"So let's do all three together."},{"time":811732,"text":"\"Fall in love,\""},{"time":813897,"text":"\"colonization\""},{"time":815845,"text":"and \"enlightenment.\""},{"time":818767,"text":"Good job, everyone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":819941,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":821183,"text":"Notice how all three signs\nare very similar,"},{"time":823445,"text":"they all happen at the head and the chest,"},{"time":825566,"text":"but they convey quite different meanings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827812,"text":"So it's amazing to see\nhow ASL is alive and thriving,"},{"time":831160,"text":"just like music is."},{"time":834152,"text":"However, in this day and age,"},{"time":837002,"text":"we live in a very audio-centric world."},{"time":839628,"text":"And just because ASL has no sound to it,"},{"time":843033,"text":"it automatically holds no social currency."},{"time":847271,"text":"We need to start thinking harder\nabout what defines social currency"},{"time":852033,"text":"and allow ASL to develop\nits own form of currency --"},{"time":855899,"text":"without sound."},{"time":858262,"text":"And this could possibly be a step\nto lead to a more inclusive society."},{"time":866291,"text":"And maybe people will understand"},{"time":868447,"text":"that you don't need\nto be deaf to learn ASL,"},{"time":872007,"text":"nor do you have to be hearing\nto learn music."}]},{"cues":[{"time":876891,"text":"ASL is such a rich treasure"},{"time":879610,"text":"that I'd like you\nto have the same experience."},{"time":882419,"text":"And I'd like to invite you\nto open your ears,"},{"time":885219,"text":"to open your eyes,"},{"time":887134,"text":"take part in our culture"},{"time":888869,"text":"and experience our visual language."},{"time":891412,"text":"And you never know,"},{"time":892871,"text":"you might just fall in love with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":894635,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":896717,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":898508,"text":"Denise Kahler-Braaten: Hey, that's me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":900433,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}